1330
01:03:50,880 --> 01:03:53,480
No, she isn't.

1331
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:55,400
Wasn't, was she.

1332
01:03:56,840 --> 01:03:58,280
He returns the hug.

1333
01:04:00,880 --> 01:04:05,400
And leads you to a communal house

1334
01:04:06,400 --> 01:04:09,619
where everybody's kind of preparing a meal.

1335
01:04:10,960 --> 01:04:15,719
You sit down with all of Mular's family.

1336
01:04:17,199 --> 01:04:21,079
Some of the kids come up and start showing you

1337
01:04:21,079 --> 01:04:22,740
different things of theirs.

1338
01:04:24,320 --> 01:04:25,880
Like kids do.

1339
01:04:25,880 --> 01:04:26,960
Look at this rock I found.

1340
01:04:26,960 --> 01:04:27,800
Kids totally do.

1341
01:04:27,800 --> 01:04:28,619
Yeah.

1342
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:32,000
That's what kids do, it's fine.

1343
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:32,880
Cool rock, kid.

1344
01:04:37,079 --> 01:04:40,320
They make a meal, everybody sits down.

1345
01:04:40,320 --> 01:04:45,320
It's a pretty somber occasion, obviously.

1346
01:04:46,719 --> 01:04:48,800
There's not much chatter that goes on

1347
01:04:48,800 --> 01:04:51,240
until the end of the night.

1348
01:04:51,240 --> 01:04:53,079
All the kids are being put to sleep.

1349
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:59,480
And everybody's tidying up and you're sitting with John Zink.

1350
01:05:02,240 --> 01:05:07,240
And he says, we hadn't seen much of New Lara

1351
01:05:08,639 --> 01:05:11,000
until she was able to come home,

1352
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:14,780
which was amazing.

1353
01:05:16,679 --> 01:05:21,679
She mentioned how much she loved the two of you.

1354
01:05:24,240 --> 01:05:29,240
And how you were, how you were family to her.

1355
01:05:34,159 --> 01:05:39,159
Thank you for making sure she wasn't alone.

1356
01:05:43,079 --> 01:05:46,280
We're sorry, we couldn't do more.

1357
01:05:46,280 --> 01:05:51,280
She told me that it was going to be something

1358
01:05:53,920 --> 01:05:57,080
that was hard won and hard fought

1359
01:05:57,080 --> 01:05:58,600
and that there was a chance

1360
01:05:58,600 --> 01:06:00,400
that she wasn't going to come back.

1361
01:06:02,720 --> 01:06:07,720
So, in some way, I was prepared for this day.

1362
01:06:09,240 --> 01:06:12,240
In other ways, you can't, you can't, you just can't.

1363
01:06:16,840 --> 01:06:21,040
But don't, don't be sorry.

1364
01:06:22,200 --> 01:06:26,000
You were with her until the end,

1365
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:28,480
fighting beside her, being with her.

1366
01:06:33,360 --> 01:06:38,280
It's really, she wasn't meant to stay here.

1367
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:43,280
She was meant to be out there adventuring, fighting,

1368
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:48,880
doing right and the outcome, as hard as it is.

1369
01:06:56,880 --> 01:07:00,680
It's what she, it's what she wanted

1370
01:07:00,680 --> 01:07:05,680
to see the world, the country free.

1371
01:07:08,880 --> 01:07:11,400
I raised my glass, I assume we have glasses.

1372
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:13,800
There's no way anyone's doing any of this sober.

1373
01:07:13,800 --> 01:07:16,240
No, I wouldn't have to think so.

1374
01:07:16,240 --> 01:07:19,240
I raise my glass and I say to new Lara,

1375
01:07:20,280 --> 01:07:21,360
she saved us all.

1376
01:07:23,559 --> 01:07:24,400
Here, here.

1377
01:07:25,440 --> 01:07:28,680
He raises his glass as well and takes a big swig.

1378
01:07:31,119 --> 01:07:33,400
So I could never ever ask before,

1379
01:07:33,400 --> 01:07:36,400
but any good embarrassing stories?

1380
01:07:41,400 --> 01:07:43,119
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.

1381
01:07:57,880 --> 01:08:00,720
The songs Nowhere Land, Lost Time, Blue Feather,

1382
01:08:00,720 --> 01:08:03,960
The Machine Thinks, and At Rest are by Kavin McLeod

1383
01:08:03,960 --> 01:08:06,280
of incompetech.filmmusic.io.
